# Atomic Design (installer)

Follow [Atomic Design methodology, chapter 2](https://atomicdesign.bradfrost.com/chapter-2/) as the mental model for the installer UI. The five stages are **atoms**, **molecules**, **organisms**, **templates**, and **pages**. This is **not a linear workflow** (“build all atoms first, then molecules…”). Treat it as a way to move between **detail** (individual pieces) and **whole** (layouts and real content) while you work.

## Mapping in this repository

| Stage | Where it lives |
| ----- | -------------- |
| **Atoms** | `installer/src/components/atoms/` — smallest meaningful UI pieces (buttons, links, badges, headlines, status, …). |
| **Molecules** | `installer/src/components/molecules/` — simple groups of elements that work as one unit (e.g. Card, step views, Flasher). |
| **Organisms** | `installer/src/components/organisms/` — distinct sections of the interface (Header, Footer, Welcome, …). |
| **Templates** | Page-level layouts focused on **structure and placeholders**, e.g. `MainApp` in `installer/src/App.tsx`, playground shells under `installer/src/playground/`. |
| **Pages** | Concrete route or screen **instances** with realistic content and states (`/`, playground routes, future routes). Use this level to test variations and resilience of the system. |

## Special folders

- **`installer/src/components/ui/`** — Thin shadcn-solid primitives. Do **not** add installer-specific domain logic here. Follow `.cursor/rules/solid-shadcn-components.mdc` for theming and composition.
- **`installer/src/components/forms/`** — Form-oriented building blocks, usually **molecule-level** (label + control + error text, e.g. `InputField.tsx`). May use `ui/` or Kobalte, but not full screens.

## Import direction

- **Atoms** must not import from `molecules/` or `organisms/`.
- **Molecules** may use atoms, `ui/`, and shared libs; must not import `organisms/`.
- **Organisms** compose lower layers as needed.
- **Exception:** Atoms may use **primitives** (Kobalte, `ui/*`) — analogous to base HTML elements in the methodology.

## New components

Prefer `atoms/`, `molecules/`, or `organisms/`. Avoid new loose files under `installer/src/components/` root unless there is a documented reason (e.g. a temporary migration).

## Tests and documentation

- Component tests: mirror `installer/src/components/` under `installer/tests/components/` (see `.cursor/rules/test-structure.mdc`).
- New or changed props: update types, hand-written docs under `installer/docs` when applicable, and generated docs per project hooks.

